version you need, you can have a look on the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/01-%E2%80%90-Available-API","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and also the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Let’s say you will use some beta version today, e.g. the version1.3.0-beta.2","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","media":"tutorial-discovery-1-ouds-swift-package.png","caption":[],"code":null},{"code":null,"media":"tutorial-discovery-1-ouds-libraries.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once you downloaded the package, you will see several librairies are available.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They can be embeded inside your ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"target","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" librairies.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Things are separated to let users integrate only what they need and embed the abre minimum of content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesContract","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" library provides the main elements like the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The theme contract is defined inside it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrange","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesSosh","type":"text"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Sosh products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesWireframe","type":"text"}]},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Wireframe theme, which is a theme dedicated to mockups and prototypes.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrangeCompact","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products but with constraints of sizes and spaces.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSComponents","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" contains the SwiftUI OUDS components defined with the Figma specifications, and also useful view modifers.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensRaw","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensSemantic","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensComponents"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are librairies defining and providing the tokens for low level (raw),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"middle level (semantic) or component levels (high level).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSModules"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" is for modules or rich components with extra logic.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSFoundations"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" is dedicated to some utilities and shared logic.","type":"text"}]}],"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add for example only the umbrella product merging all products mentioned above: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSSwiftUI"}],"type":"emphasis"}]}],"type":"step","runtimePreview":null}],"contentSection":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS for iOS is an open source Swift Package available on GitHub under MIT license.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The package and the librairies must be added through Xcode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia"}],"anchor":"Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"}]},{"kind":"assessments","assessments":[{"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Which of these choices is correct?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[],"choices":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"I can contribute to OUDS using pull request","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS is open source, under MIT license, and hosted on GitHub. Of course you can contribute!","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS supports officialy all Apple OS like visionOS, tvOS, watchOS, iPadOS, iOS and also CarPlay.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The main supported targets are iOS \/ iPadOS. However we do our best to support macOS, visionOS, tvOS and watchOS.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"CarPlay specific cases are not scoped yet.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides UIKit components","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS supports only SwiftUI.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"multiple-choice"},{"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Which imports of the OUDS Swift Package products can I choose?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[],"choices":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some of the available products depending to my needs, or only ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if I am very lazy and don’t care about my app size.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can import all products provided by the Swift Package, and tailor your choice to keep only the ones needed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Even if we recommend to choose only the atomic products you need, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" product wraps all of them.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"None, only the Swift package dependency matter.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You need to chose the products the Swift package provides.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"multiple-choice"}],"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding"},{"kind":"callToAction","title":"Instanciate and inject a theme","action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme","overridingTitle":"Get started","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}]},"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The theme is exposed as one object which will be injected inside your SwiftUI view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The theme provides all tokens which defines in the end the rendering of everything."}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"project","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies"]}],"references":{"https://github.com/Orange-OpenSource/ouds-ios/releases":{"title":"GitHub releases","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub releases"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases","url":"htt